intro brand product

about

Statemints (product of Jogg) is a web application that allows you to discover, highlight & curate the insights most valuable to you, sourced from incredible conversations and events.



The goal for Statemints is to enable a platform for clients to store large archives of media files (video or audio) and offer them as a resource for their audience to view and create highlight montages with.

responsibilities

Role

Chief Creative Officer

At this time, Jogg was growing as a company, and as the creative director, I lead a team of 2 other designers in the creation of this Statemints. We worked closely with the developers to map out the user experience and build an application with high functionality and a simple interface.

brand

When deciding on a direction for the identity of Statemints, we concluded that we wanted the brand to reflect a more professional and practical design, as opposed to the more fun and social appearance of Jogg Studio’s design.

At the same time, we still wanted to maintain some sort of connection between the branding of Statemints and the branding of Jogg and its other products. To achieve this, we created the Statemints logo out of the parts of the Jogg company logo (the three stadiums and the circle) and rearranged them to represent the main feature of Statemints - highlighting and creating notepads from the vast library of content provided.

components

Working on Statemints gave me the opportunity to explore more ways with prototyping interactive components in Figma. Doing so gave us a way to communicate more clearly what the vision was for various animations and interactions.

product

Statemints Vault (originally Sessions) is the client-facing side of Statemints. This is where brands can upload large libraries of long form video and audio files to be viewed and highlighted by subscribers.



Statemints is the consumer-facing side of the product, where subscribers of a brand can view content, create highlights, and compile montages (referred to as “statemints”) out of highlight clips.

vault

On the Statemints Vault side of the product, brands would create folders & categories to hold their media files. In this example, the brand, Comic Expo, holds conventions every year and uses Statemints Vault to archive their recordings of panels, trailers, etc. from each event. They organize their files into folders with the location of the event (Comic Expo Los Angeles) and categories with the year of the event (Comic Expo LA 2023).



Brands have full control over who can access their uploads. They can upload a list of email addresses to a whitelist, so that any user that signs up for Statemints with that an email on that list will be given access to the brand’s content. In this example, Comic Expo can import a list of all the people who have purchased badges for the convention.
